cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.COM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a power control scheme for uplink cellular networks, which is a networking topic.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the trade-off between received signal strength and interference, which is related to information theory.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a coordinated power control scheme for cellular systems, which involves control and optimization.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper evaluates the throughput performance of the proposed scheme on an LTE system-level simulation platform, which involves multimedia traffic.
- cs.COM (Computers and Society) is the least likely category as the paper does not discuss any social or ethical implications of the proposed scheme.
